   abstract = {The agronomic axis of the PhytoCOTE project had a primary objective of evaluating the phytosanitary pressure in the field and the risks of pesticide transfers to surface waters. But also a second objective to assess the performance of existing wine systems and propose scenarios for changing production methods and practices to reduce the use of pesticides. To do this, around forty wine-growing systems on farms belonging to different driving modes were investigated. These systems were evaluated using a multi-criteria decision support analysis method belonging to the ELECTRE methods: Electre Tri-C. Six evaluation criteria were selected on the one hand for socio-economic performance (economic profitability, workload, complexity of the wine system); on the other hand for environmental performance (phytosanitary pressure, ecotoxicity of pesticides, agro-ecological practices, level of product drift)
